The harmonic sum \( H_n \) is expressed as \( \frac{h_n}{k_n} \), where \( h_n \) and \( k_n \) are coprime. The least common multiple \( L_n \) is the smallest number divisible by each of the numbers from 1 to \( n \). By examining the denominators \( k_n \) for each \( n \): - For \( n = 1 \) to \( n = 5 \), \( k_n = L_n \), so \( k_n \) is not less than \( L_n \). - Starting from \( n = 6 \), \( k_n \) becomes less than \( L_n \) due to the reduced form of the harmonic sum.
